************************************************************************************************************************
							Knowledge Discovery Process
************************************************************************************************************************

Problem Definition                     : Define the problem and desired result
Data collection                        : Collect the relevant data from various sources
Data Preprocessing                     : Remove redundant data & Clean for further preprocessing
Feature removal or dimension reduction : Remove redundant features
Data transformation                    : Transform the data or change the scale of data
Data mining                            : Data insight and new variable creation
Data analysis                          : Statistical analysis of data
Data visualisation                     : Visualize the data and try to find pattern in dataset



************************************************************************************************************************
                            			Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
************************************************************************************************************************
Variable Identification
Univariate Analysis
Bi-variate Analysis
Missing values treatment
Outlier treatment
Variable transformation
Variable creation
Feature Removal or Dimension Reduction


1. Variable Identification
	Predictor
	Target
	Data types
	Nominal 
	Ordinal
	Qualitative
	Quantitative
	Continuous
	Descrete

2. Univariate Analysis	
	Continuous Variables	
		Central tendency
		Spread/Range 
		Missing Value detection
		Outliers Detection
		Distribution
		Graphical visualisation
		Descriptive statistics
	Categorical variables	
		Frequency
		Distribution of each category
		Graphical visualisation
		Descriptive statistics

3. Bi-variate Analysis:	 Relationship b/w two variables, Association/dissociation b/w variables	
	Continuous & Continuous	
		Graphical visualisation
		Correlation
	Categorical & Categorical	
		Two way table
		Stacked column chart 
		Bar chart
		Chi-square Test
	Categorical & Continuous	
		Z-Test
		T-Test
		ANOVA

4. Missing values treatment	
	Deletion	
		List wise deletion 
		Pair wise deletion 
		Deleting Coloumn
	Imputation	
		Mean/Meadian/Mode
		Generalized imputation
		Similar case Imputation
		Prediction model	
		K-nearest Imputation	

5. Outlier treatment	
	Outlier Cause 	
		Data entry error
		Measurement error
		Experimental error
		Intentional outlier 
		Data processing error
		Sampling error
		Natural outlier 
	Detect outlier 	
		Box plot 
		Histogram plot
		Scatter plot
	 	-1.5*IQR to +1.5*IQR
		Out of 5th to 95th percentile
	Outlier removal	Deleting observation
		Transforming & binning values
		Imputing
		Treat seperately

6. Variable transformation
	Change the scale
		Min-Max scaling : x/(max-min) or (x-min)/(max-min)
		Mean Normalization : (x-mean)/(max-min)
		Standardization(Z-Score Normalization): Zero mean and unit variance   (x-mean)/std
		Label encoding
		One-hot encoding
	Symmetric distribution over skewed distribution
	Apply standard transformation (log, square_root, cube_root ...)
	Binning

7. Variable creation
	Derived variables
	Dummy variable 

